<h2>
    Introduction to Pink Salmon
</h2>
<p>
    Pink salmon, also known as humpback salmon, are the smallest species in the Pacific salmon family. Their life cycle spans two years, which is why they return to spawn every odd-numbered year—including 2025.
</p>
<p>
    They're easily recognizable by their light pink hue and the distinct hump males develop during spawning. These fish migrate from the Pacific Ocean into Oregon’s rivers to spawn, making inland areas like Salem ideal for freshwater fishing action during their brief return.
</p>
<h2>
    2025 Pink Salmon Run Forecast
</h2>
<p>
    This year’s pink salmon run near Salem is expected to begin in <strong>early August</strong>, with numbers peaking in <strong>late August to early September</strong>. According to recent <strong>ODFW (Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife)</strong> projections, the return looks promising, thanks to cooler ocean temperatures and improved juvenile survival rates in the past cycle.
</p>
<p>
    Stay updated via the ODFW Fishing Report for weekly salmon run updates and river conditions.
</p>
