<h2>
    When to Fish for Pink Salmon
</h2>
<p>
    The pink salmon season in Oregon typically starts in <strong>August</strong> and runs through <strong>early October</strong>. The best time to fish is:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Early Morning</strong>: 6 AM to 9 AM
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Late Afternoon</strong>: 4 PM to dusk
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    During cloudy days or after a light rain, pinks become more active, especially in shaded river sections.
</p>
<h2>
    Daily and Weekly Tides and Timing
</h2>
<p>
    Though Salem isn’t tidal, the timing of fish movement upstream is often tied to ocean tides. Pink salmon surge into river mouths during high tides and continue their journey inland for days after.
</p>
<p>
    Use tools like <strong>Tide Charts</strong> for Astoria or Newport to predict when pushes of salmon might reach upriver zones.
</p>
