</h2>
<p>
    <strong>Q1: Do pink salmon run every year in Oregon?</strong><br>
    No. Pink salmon return to spawn every <strong>odd-numbered year</strong>, making 2025 the ideal time to fish for them.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q2: Are pink salmon good to eat?</strong><br>
    Yes, though they are leaner than Chinook or Coho. Best when fresh, smoked, or canned shortly after catching.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q3: Can I fish for pink salmon from the bank?</strong><br>
    Absolutely. Many spots near Salem are bank-friendly and productive, especially Wallace Marine Park and Mission Bottom.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q4: What’s the best bait for pink salmon?</strong><br>
    Pink or chartreuse jigs, small spoons, or flies work best. Add scent attractants for better results.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q5: Do I need a salmon tag in Oregon?</strong><br>
    Yes. Along with your fishing license, you must carry a valid salmon/steelhead tag and report your harvest.
</p>
<p>
